{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"11427ee7-f56d-4085-adc8-ab7587320261","content":"The `.testsettings` format is **legacy** and ignored by MSTest v3+. You need to migrate to a `.runsettings` file. Here's what your settings translate to:\n\n| `.testsettings` setting | `.runsettings` equivalent |\n|---|---|\n| `TestTimeout=30000` | `<TestTimeout>30000</TestTimeout>` in `<MSTest>` |\n| Code Coverage collector | `<DataCollector>` in `<DataCollectionRunSettings>` |\n| `AssemblyResolution` | No longer needed (handled by the SDK) |","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01DtSYP9SZsdRPTR2EcmGePZ","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Creating .runsettings file"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01MA4ozP7x45UKacVSBrFhd4","name":"create","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-d2cc46a8468c4b32bc39e81ee689a86d/local.runsettings","file_text":"<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n<RunSettings>\n  <MSTest>\n    <TestTimeout>30000</TestTimeout>\n  </MSTest>\n  <DataCollectionRunSettings>\n    <DataCollectors>\n      <DataCollector friendlyName=\"Code Coverage\"\n        uri=\"datacollector://Microsoft/CodeCoverage/2.0\"\n        assemblyQualifiedName=\"Microsoft.VisualStudio.TraceCollector.CoverageCollectorDataCollector, Microsoft.VisualStudio.TraceCollector, Culture=neutral, PublicKeyToken=b03f5f7f11d50a3a\">\n        <Configuration>\n          <CodeCoverage />\n        </Configuration>\n      </DataCollector>\n    </DataCollectors>\n  </DataCollectionRunSettings>\n</RunSettings>\n"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"create a new file at /tmp/sv-d2cc46a8468c4b32bc39e81ee689a86d/local.runsettings."}],"interactionId":"2d5576d5-2871-4eb9-9174-414ffcae6465","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has a `.testsettings` file which is the legacy format. Modern MSTest (v3+) uses `.runsettings` instead. Let me explain the migration and create the equivalent `.runsettings` file.\n\nThe `.testsettings` file contains:\n1. Assembly resolution with